<note id="fs-id1167662784622" class="microbiology disease-profile">
<title>Acellular Infections of the Nervous System</title>
<para id="fs-id1167662473611">Serious consequences are the common thread among these neurological diseases. Several cause debilitating paralysis, and some, such as Creutzfeldt-Jakob disease and rabies, are always or nearly always fatal. Since few drugs are available to combat these infections, vector control and vaccination are critical for prevention and containment. <link target-id="OSC_Microbio_26_03_AcelTBL"/> summarizes some important viral and prion infections of the nervous system.</para>
